This paper deals with maintaining quantile sketches for large, distributed data streams, which is a problem commonly studied in the sub-fields of data structures (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the importance of mergeability, which is a property relevant to systems (cs.SY) and networking (cs.NE).
